In python the textwrap module is used to format and wrap plain texts. There are some options to format the texts by adjusting the line breaks in the input paragraph. 
To use these modules, we need to import the textwrap module in our code. 
    ->The user first inputs a non-spaced string.
    ->Then, in the second line, the user inputs the permissible width for each row.
    ->The output will execute wrapped text.
    
    
#Example:
If the user inputs abcd in the first line and 2 in the second line, then the output will be:
ab
cd

#Program
from textwrap import fill
n=input()
m=int(input())
print(fill(n,m))
